      <para styleclass="Heading1">Error XS1721</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Class &apos;class&apos; cannot have multiple base classes: &apos;class_1&apos; and &apos;class_2&apos;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The most common cause of this error message is attempting to use multiple inheritance. A class in X# may only inherit directly from one class. However, a class can implement any number of interfaces.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
